title: How To Deploy facebook.com
description:
In this seminar, we'll cover the basic building blocks of infrastructure management and SRE duties by drawing parallels between Facebook and other big tech companies and analyzing them.

Systems Engineering, SRE and this field as a whole is seldom covered by workshops or courses at UCSD, yet is becoming more of a part of standard SWE positions over time, whilst also paying significantly higher on average. title: Intro to Neurosecurity
description: Infosec meets brain-machine interface! Direct brain-machine interface (BMI) has moved from science fiction to daily fact, and a new frontier of Infosec is emerging: neurosecurity. Invasive and non-invasive BMIs now augment operators in many walks of life. Entirely new attack surfaces are therefore available to be exploited by malicious cyber-criminals, making the security of these devices of paramount importance, and not a consideration to be ignored until these attacks have already occurred. This presentation will chronicle and categorize present and near-future threats, known and potential countermeasures, and cut through hyperbole and sensationalism to expose and discuss the reality of the emerging neurosecurity landscape.

ACM at UCSD is back at it with a ton of new events, opportunities, and PRIZES at our Spring Kickoff! Join us to see what workshops and socials we have in store this quarter, participate in our newly expanding Projects, and find out how to join ACM's 2021-2021 Leadership!
This kickoff, we're partnering with Optiver to provide y'all with internship opportunities and X lucky winners will be receiving RAFFLE PRIZES, so you won't want to miss it!

A message from our sponsors at Optiver:
Optiver is a global proprietary market maker, trading on all major financial markets around the world. During this event you will learn the ins-and-outs of Optiver, and how your unique skillsets can contribute to our Software Engineer or Quantitative Trader team. This talk will be hosted by Optiver‚Äôs Trader Education Lead, Randall Laurence.
Randall Laurence has been with Optiver for 12 years and has been the Trader Education Lead for the past 5. He is responsible for our Trader education program that all Traders and Software Engineers participate in before they get started on a team. Randall has a unique background as an Actuarial Scientist and loves bringing in new Optiverians from diverse STEM backgrounds.
Optiver has mentioned that they will be sending out a link for internship priority, allowing students who apply to get their resumes will be reviewed first! So come to kickoff for a chance to work at this exciting company!
